MongoDB :

- Non-Relational Database stores data in JSON format.
- MongoDB is document oriented No-SQL database system.
- it is an open source and cross-platform database system.

BSON data :

- Binary Json(only machines can read).
- when we give JSON data to MongoDB it converts it into BSON data and then stored it in memory.

Document :

- Mongo stores data in the form of documents (BSON docs),

Collection : - MongoDB stores documents in collections.

# show collection - shows all collection in database.
